File: Raindrops seen on a window. AFP/Tauseef Mustafa PRETORIA - The weather service is warning of heavy rainfall in Northern Gauteng, including Pretoria from midday on Tuesday. There are threats of localised flooding, poor visibility and bad driving conditions. WATCH : Gauteng floods | Hundreds left homeless At the same time, heavy rain has been falling in parts of KwaZulu-Natal. The N3 Toll Concession has reported drizzle in certain parts. It's warning motorists to drive carefully.